<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="545">
<subfield code="a">
Photographer, filmmaker, musician, designer, folklorist, and writer John Cohen was born in 1932 in Queens, New York. As a founder of the revivalist string band, New Lost City Ramblers, Cohen participated and documented the folk music scene of New York City, while also extending his photographic eye to the Avant Garde art and literary scenes of the late 1950s and 1960s. His varied interests led him to take many collecting trips on which he recorded, photographed, and made films primarily about Peruvian and Appalachian music and culture. His photographs have been widely published and featured in exhibits across the United States and in Peru and England. He was married to Penelope (Penny) Seeger (1943-1993). Cohen died in 2019.
</subfield>
</datafield>
